<http://dx.doi.org/10.1206/830.1>
    bibo:endPage "71" ;
    bibo:issue "382" ;
    bibo:journal "Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2013-12-02" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "2013" ;
    dc:creator "González-Santillán, Edmundo; Prendini, Lorenzo" ;
    dc:date "2013" ;
    dc:title "Redefinition And Generic Revision Of The North American Vaejovid Scorpion Subfamily Syntropinae Kraepelin, 1905, With Descriptions Of Six New Genera" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4611869>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4611881>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4611887>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4611919>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4611927>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4611931> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4611869>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Representative species in the North American vaejovid scorpion subfamily Syntropinae Kraepelin, 1905. A. Chihuahuanus bilineatus (Pocock, 1898), comb. nov., ♀; B. Kochius bruneus (Williams, 1970), 8; C. Mesomexovis punctatus (Karsch, 1879), comb. nov., 8; D. Syntropis macrura Kraepelin, 1900, ♀; E. Thorellius sp., 8; F. Vizcaino viscainensis (Williams, 1970), comb. nov., 8. Photos in B, D and E courtesy of R. Mercurio." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4611869/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4611881>
    dc:description "Fig. 5. Map of southwestern North America, plotting known locality records for two genera in the vaejovid scorpion subfamily Syntropinae Kraepelin, 1905, based on data collected in the present study: Kochius Soleglad and Fet, 2008 (circles); Thorellius Soleglad and Fet, 2008 (squares)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4611881/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4611887>
    dc:description "Fig. 7. Most parsimonious tree (length: 10894.593, CI: 0.190, RI: 0.628, fit: 244.08), obtained by simultaneous phylogenetic analysis of 250 qualitative and quantitative morphological characters and 4221 aligned DNA nucleotides from three mitochondrial and two nuclear gene markers, for 18 genera and 61 species in the North American vaejovid scorpion subfamily Syntropinae Kraepelin, 1905. Analyses were conducted with an implied weighting regime (k 518) that maximized average support (González-Santillán and Prendini, in press). Synapomorphies are optimized with accelerated transformation. Black bars indicate uniquely derived apomorphic states, white bars indicate parallel derivations of apomorphic states, numbers above indicate characters, and numbers below indicate states (appendix 1)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4611887/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4611919>
    dc:description "Fig. 17. Syntropinae Kraepelin, 1905, dextral pedipalp chela, dorsal (A, C) and retrolateral (B, D) aspects, illustrating carinae and distribution of trichobothria. A, B. Chihuahuanus crassimanus (Pocock, 1898), comb. nov., 8 (AMNH). C, D. Thorellius intrepidus (Thorell, 1876), 8 (AMNH). Scale bars 5 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4611919/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4611927>
    dc:description "Fig. 20. Syntropinae Kraepelin, 1905, dextral pedipalp chela movable finger, dorsal aspect, illustrating dentition. A. Balsateres cisnerosi (Ponce-Saavedra and Sissom, 2004), comb. nov., 8 (IBUNAM). B. Thorellius intrepidus (Thorell, 1876), 8 (AMNH). C. Vizcaino viscainensis (Williams, 1970), comb. nov., 8 (AMNH). Scale bars 5 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4611927/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4611931>
    dc:description "Fig. 21. Syntropinae Kraepelin, 1905, dextral leg III, basitarsus and telotarsus, ventral aspect, illustrating macrosetae and spinules. A. Chihuahuanus globosus (Borelli, 1915), comb. nov., 8 (AMNH). B. Thorellius intrepidus (Thorell, 1876), 8 (AMNH). C. Vizcaino viscainensis (Williams, 1970), comb. nov., 8 (AMNH). Scale bars 5 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4611931/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

